Third-party data, models, and services
================================================================================

This repository contains SOURCE CODE ONLY. It ships no patient data and no
model weights. The platform depends on the following third-party resources,
which users must obtain themselves under their own respective licenses:

1. MIMIC-IV (Medical Information Mart for Intensive Care IV)
   - Source: PhysioNet (https://physionet.org/content/mimiciv/)
   - License: PhysioNet Credentialed Health Data License 1.5.0
   - Requires CITI "Data or Specimens Only Research" training + a signed DUA.
   - NOT redistributable. See docs/DATA_ACCESS.md.

2. Large Language Models (pulled at runtime via Ollama; not vendored here)
   - Meta Llama 3.2 — Llama 3.2 Community License ("Built with Llama").
   - DeepSeek-R1 (distill) — MIT weights over a Llama base.
   - Google MedGemma / Gemma — Gemma Terms of Use + Health AI Developer
     Foundations terms ("not for clinical use").
   - OpenBioLLM — Llama 3 Community License (research-oriented).
   See docs/MODELS.md for each model's license and acceptable-use terms.

3. Runtime infrastructure services (pulled as containers, invoked over the
   network — not linked into this codebase): MongoDB, Redis, Prometheus,
   Grafana, Loki, Redpanda, OpenTelemetry Collector, Jaeger. Each retains its
   own license; none is imposed on this project's source.

